title.rendered: Justin Bieber to Reprise Role on CSI

content.rendered:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

Justin Bieber has found time in his busy making out schedule to return to one of TV’s top-rated dramas.

The singer, who appeared on the September season premiere of CSI as troubled teen Jason McCann, will reprise this role on February 17. On an episode titled “Targets of Obsession,” Bieber’s character will contact George Eads’s Nick because he’s in “imminent danger,” according to a network press release.

The guest-starring stint will coincide with the release of Never Say Never, the Justin biopic that hits theaters on February 11.

Check out a clip from it NOW!
